# SignalFit — Cursor Rules
# Miami Cursor Hackathon · Build & Ship Track

## Project
SignalFit is a wellness reflection app. Users log food, sleep, training, and how they feel.
We derive nutrition from meals and use an LLM to surface possible patterns between habits and performance.
**Not medical advice. Wellness reflection only.**

## Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Supabase (Postgres + auth)
- OpenAI GPT-4o (structured JSON output)
- Tailwind CSS
- Vercel (deploy)

## Architecture
```
Browser form
  → POST /api/insight
    → resolveNutrition(meals, supabase.foods)
    → OpenAI GPT-4o (JSON mode)
    → insert into supabase.logs
  → Insight UI
```

## Key Files
- `app/api/insight/route.ts` — main API route (Role 3)
- `app/page.tsx` — multi-step form (Role 2)
- `data/demo-bad-recovery-day.json` — demo scenario (Role 5)
- `data/foods.json` — food lookup (Role 5)
- `supabase/migrations/` — schema (Role 3)
- `supabase/seed/` — seed data (Role 5)

## API Contract
Request shape: goal, weight_lb, sleep, nutrition_input, training, wellbeing, notes, recent_days
Response shape: recovery_status, readiness_score, main_insight, summary, what_is_helping,
  what_is_hurting, possible_connections, signals, today_action_plan, tomorrow_focus,
  reflection_question, safety_note

**Do not rename response fields without team agreement.**

## Language Rules (AI Safety)
The LLM prompt must always use:
- "possible pattern", "may suggest", "based on what you logged"
- "worth noticing", "appears to line up with"
Never use:
- Certainty claims ("this means", "you have", "you need")
- Medical language ("diagnosis", "treatment", "condition")
- Fear-based framing or body shaming
- Supplement pushing or extreme diet advice
Always include `safety_note` in every response.

## Cursor Behavior
- Always write TypeScript, never plain JS in app/
- Use `?.` optional chaining — many fields are optional
- Never expose ANTHROPIC_API_KEY or SUPABASE_ANON_KEY to the browser
- All LLM calls go through /api/insight — never call OpenAI from the client
- Use `response_format: { type: 'json_object' }` on all OpenAI calls
- Wrap LLM JSON.parse in try/catch and fall back to canned response
- Don't await Supabase log inserts — fire and forget so user isn't waiting
- Demo button loads data/demo-bad-recovery-day.json into form state
- nutrition object is always server-computed, never sent from the form

